attributes.title: Glowstone Palace
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Lindsay check out one of the most well lit builds ever featured in this week's MegaCraft!

attributes.title: Airship Attack
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Jeremy look at airships attacking a giant monster. I can't even think of anything witty to say here. Damn I'm tired.

attributes.title: NotchLand
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Lindsay check out a crazy Minecraft themed amusement park!

attributes.title: Majora's Mask Clocktown
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Kerry visit a minecraft map in another dimension that borrows assets from our own. That's right it's Majora's Mask's Clocktown!

attributes.title: Chrota's End
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Jeremy head to Minecraft's moon to see if killing Chrota in Minecraft is easier than it is in Destiny. It is in case anyone was wondering.

attributes.title: Five Nights at Freddy's
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt, Jeremy, and the always surprising Joel check out a recreation of the horrifying pizza survival game, Five Nights at Freddy's, in Minecraft!

attributes.title: Westeroscraft Winterfell
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Geoff check out Westeroscraft! For this first day we're going to head to Winterfell and get a feel for it before everything terrible happens to it.

attributes.title: Westeroscraft The Wall
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Joel are back for day two of Westeroscraft! Today they're checking out The Wall and all things north of it to see if a blocky version matches up to the real thing. White Walkers not included.

attributes.title: The Vale
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Geoff are back for day three of Westeroscraft! Today they're heading to The Vale and jumping out of the famous Moon Door.

attributes.title: Westeroscraft The Twins and Riverrun
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Trevor are here for day four of Westeroscraft! Today they're checking out some of the best bridges in Westeros, The Twins and Riverrun.

attributes.title: Westeroscraft Dragonstone, Pyke, and Sunspear
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Jack tackle day five of Westeroscraft! Today they cover a lot of ground by checking out Dragonstone, Pyke, and Sunspear.

attributes.title: Westeroscraft Casterly Rock and Harrenhall
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt, Joel, and Adam, take on day six of our Westeroscraft special! Today they head to Casterly Rock and Harrenhall to see what it is about those places that makes the Lannisters jerks.

attributes.title: Westeroscraft King's Landing
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Geoff are back for the final day of our Westeroscraft special! For the last day they're heading to the biggest city in all of Westeros, King's Landing.

attributes.title: Mega Jack's House
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Jack check out MrBuildsALot's tribute to Jack and his house. It's a solid 4 out of 10, you should check it out.

attributes.title: Avenger's City
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Jack visit a city ravenged by war and a few dudes in shiny costumes.

attributes.title: The Battle of Hoth
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt, Adam, and Joel visit a galaxy far far away in the present and check out Hypixel's Incredible Battle of Hoth Adventure map!

attributes.title: Adventure Time Ice Kingdom
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt and Lindsay return to the world of Adventure Time and check out the Ice Kingdom!

attributes.title: Adventure Time: Fire Kingdom

attributes.title: Embarrassing Pictures of Achievement Hunter
attributes.caption: Minecraft
attributes.description: Matt, Geoff, Jack, and Ryan check out some faithful recreations of some of their more embarrassing moments.
